<section>
  <h2>Language and Communication</h2>
  <p>
    If one were to pass through, Jamestown it is likely that the conversations would be dominatly English. But Jamestown had the prescence of other languages: African languages brought by slaves and of curse, the native tongue of the Powhatan people.   
  </p>
  <p>
    The colony also produced some of the earliest English writings in America, such as the detailed journals of Captain John Smith, which provide invaluable insight into the cultural mindset of the time. His maps are also a great win for historians as they are able to deduce much of the topography of the surrounding area.
  </p>
