<section>
  <h2>Arts and Traditions</h2>
  <p>
    What is Art? How can we define it or describe what it means to a society? 
    Well, Art can be anything which moves an audience to strong emotion due to a certain type of concious experience. This working definition is broad and includes things like music, storytelling, sketching etc. The settlers learned from the natives and the result was a sycretism of art.
  </p>
  <p>
    Archaeological discoveries have revealed artifacts such as pottery and religious items, highlighting how settlers preserved cultural identity amidst hardship. For an archaeological perspective, see <a href="https://www.nps.gov/jame/learn/historyculture/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">National Park Service: Jamestown Archaeology</a>.
